Text.Value:
To passions brash thou art a slave.
This sinful ground shall be thy grave.

Thine offering is doomed to lack,
So face a fate most bleak and black.
I offer myself.
How about some gold? I've got plenty.

Return to me with what I seek,
Or face a fate most black and bleak.

A grasping hand, an offering vile...
Enter now the Dread Lord's Trial.
Grant unto me a touch more time / To ponder on your cunning rhyme.

A battle won, a rival slain.
His blood runs thick, a worthy stain.

Thou hast shown proof of worthy kill.
Present thyself before Bhaal's will.
I've got several powerful magic artefacts you can take.

A chosen butcher walks anew.
Thou standest 'mongst a bloody few.
I offer myself. There is no finer offering than the poison fruit of Bhaal's loins.
Ugh. Father's servants are such a bore. Let me through!
I am preparing a triumphant offering, grant me more time to make it glorious.

Thou walkest 'pon unhallowed ground,
A place your corpse will not be found.
I killed to be here - and took the victim's hand as proof.

Present me well from gifts thine own,
Or I shall rend thy flesh from bone.
I don't want to give you the wrong answer. Can I have some time to think?
I care not for what you seek. Stand aside.
I can't rend your flesh, but I can dent your metal.
Clearly, you seek me, the scion of Bhaal himself.
You seek me. Let me pass.

Synopsis: Dialog with the Death Knight sentry guarding the courtroom of the Murder Tribunal, in an underground area beneath Baldur's Gate. If you know that this is where you become an Unholy Assassin - and you have a victim's hand with you - he will let you through to be judged by the tribunal.
